snippet.title: Using technology to facilitate COVID-19 vaccinations in India with Bhavesh Bhatt #IamaGDE
snippet.description:
Meet Bhavesh Bhatt, a Google Developer Expert in Machine Learning from Mumbai, India. Bhavesh shares his latest creation, a Python script that helps people check the available slots for COVID-19 vaccination centers from the CoWIN API in India. Discover his YouTube channel, advice he has for developers, and how he leveled up his knowledge in Google Cloud and TensorFlow in this video!

Read his #IamaGDE story  → https://goo.gle/2ZgxaUM
Check out Bhavesh’s YouTube channel → https://goo.gle/BhaveshBhatYT 

Learn more about the Experts → https://goo.gle/gde-program
Follow the GDE Program → https://goo.gle/2LpWdeK

snippet.title: Preview Mobile SDK for Matter
snippet.description:
To make smart home app experiences more seamless, the Google Home Mobile SDK makes it easy to build Matter apps on Android. With this intuitive tool, you can build apps with consistent device commissioning and sharing experiences, creating great out of box experiences that quickly connect devices to Google Home and your apps. 

Learn about how Google is supporting Matter on Android through Google Play services, and preview the Google Home Mobile SDK and accompanying user journey in this session.

Resources:
Google Home → https://goo.gle/google-home
Control your smart home → https://goo.gle/smart-home
Google Smart Home support → https://goo.gle/google-home-support

Speaker: James Romo

Watch more:
Watch all the Smart Home Summit sessions → https://goo.gle/smarthomesummit-all

Subscribe to Google Developers → https://goo.gle/developers

snippet.title: Building great experiences with Google Smart Home | Developer Keynote
snippet.description:
Whether you are writing firmware for your devices, or building mobile applications to create new experiences for your users, join Marco Cavalli, Product Manager, and Jung-Yu (Gina) Yeh, Technical Solutions Engineer on the Nest team, to learn how Google is making it easy for you to integrate with Google Home.

In this session we provide an overview of the tools and solutions that Google is building to enable you to integrate with Google Home quickly and reliably. Google Home developer tools simplify complexity and merge seamlessly into your existing workflows, so that you can focus on what matters the most: creating innovative solutions that delight your customers.

Resources:
Google Home → https://goo.gle/google-home
Control your smart home → https://goo.gle/smart-home
Google Home IDE → https://goo.gle/google-home-ide
Test Suite → https://goo.gle/test-suite
Google Home Playground → https://goo.gle/google-home-playground
Webrtc Validator → https://goo.gle/webrtc-validator
Google Smart Home support → https://goo.gle/google-home-support

Speakers: Marco Cavalli • Gina Yeh

snippet.title: Smart Home Summit ‘21 Welcome Keynote
snippet.description:
Join Michele Turner, Senior Director of Product Management, to learn why Google is the best platform for smart home developers to build, innovate, and grow. 
 
We’ll show you new ways Google is empowering developers to create experiences that let users do more with your devices across Android, Nest, the Google Home app, and Google Assistant. We’ll preview upcoming tools, including two new SDKS, to build your next devices and apps using Matter and Thread — technologies that are transforming the smart home industry.
